Everyday workflow:
Working directory -> git add -> staging (index buffer ) -> git commit -> committed into repo 


Git commands:

Git config - set user/email/text editor = customising git 
Git help <command> = built in docs

Git init -> starts new git repo = this is step 1 and pushing to GitHub is step 2 
Git add -> adds changes to staging area 
Git commit -> adds staged changes to repo 

Git diff -> shows u the difference between working directory and staging area 
Git diff --staged = compare staged changes with last commit 

Git log -> commit history with names and id’s
Git log --oneline --graph = visual summary of commit history 
Git log —oneline —graph —all = compact visual full view 

Git revert - creates a new commit undoing the last commit 

Git clone - copy a remote repo on local setup 
Git rm - remove files 
Git mv - rename folders 
Git restore - undo file changes = if there is a conflict

Git blame <file> = who changed each line 
Git reflog = view local HEAD history 
